This paper is about biomedical named entity recognition (NER) using FLAIR embeddings. FLAIR is a natural language processing model, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the comparison of FLAIR with other models like BERT, which are deep learning models falling under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of pretraining and combining models, which are common techniques in information retrieval (cs.IR) and neural networks (cs.NE). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, and cs.NE.
